2025-09-29 11:07:19,984 - INFO - Strategy Summary: Reducing aspirate and dispense speeds appeared to correlate with lower deviation and variability. Higher dispense wait times also seemed to improve performance. There was a trade-off between time and performance, with faster speeds generally leading to higher deviation and variability. The recommendations aim to balance these factors for improved overall performance.
