2025-09-29 11:07:57,353 - INFO - Strategy Summary: The key insight from the data is that a balance between accuracy, precision, and efficiency can be achieved with mid-range aspirate and dispense speeds, aspirate wait time around 10 seconds, and dispense wait time around 20 to 25 seconds. Lowering the aspirate wait time and increasing the retract speed slightly may further improve performance. However, these recommendations come with various degrees of confidence and predicted improvements. Further testing is needed to confirm these findings.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,353 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 1:
2025-09-29 11:07:57,353 - INFO -   Confidence Level: high
2025-09-29 11:07:57,353 - INFO -   Reasoning: Experiment 7 in the data has the lowest deviation and variability, indicating high accuracy and precision. Although it takes relatively longer time, it is a necessary trade-off for better accuracy and precision.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,353 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: We expect the deviation to be around 8.2 and variability around 1.41, with a trade-off in time around 51.82 seconds.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 2:
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Confidence Level: medium
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Reasoning: Experiment 5 in the data shows a balance between deviation, variability, and time. The aspirate speed and dispense speed are near the middle of the range, which could be a factor in this balance.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: We expect the deviation to be around 9.78, variability around 2.48, and time around 49.58 seconds.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 3:
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Confidence Level: low
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Reasoning: Experiment 10 in the data shows a lower deviation and variability than the other experiments with higher dispense speed. The slightly lowered aspirate wait time and slightly increased retract speed may be factors in this.
2025-09-29 11:07:57,354 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: We expect the deviation to be around 12.58, variability around 2.73, and time around 45.18 seconds.
